{
  "answer": "**Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 14: *Aaftab* (The Sun)**[^1]\n\n> [p-77dda1] The Sun  \n> \n> [p-96b3da] O Sun! Thou art the world's own soul, its flowing grace,  \n> Who binds the scattered leaves of all of Time and Space.  \n> \n> [p-0d24a0] Thou art the cause that Being from Unbeing flows,  \n> And by Thy breath, the garden of Existence grows.  \n> \n> [p-df7250] This pageant of the elements by Thee is held,  \n> The urge for life in every single thing compelled.  \n> \n> [p-2f123e] From Thy bright splendor, all things find their stable state,  \n> Thy fire and harmony are life incarnate.  \n> \n> [p-fdcce3] That Sun, whose light makes all the world so bright,  \n> Is Heart, is Mind, is Soul, is conscious Light.  \n> \n> [p-af377c] O Sun, on us the light of consciousness bestow,  \n> And make our eye of reason with Thy radiance glow.  \n> \n> [p-d7151b] For all Existence, Thou dost furnish and adorn,  \n> The Lord of all on high and low, of night and morn.  \n> \n> [p-b3de7e] Thy own perfection is in every living heart,  \n> Thy splendor shown in mountain ranges set apart.  \n> \n> [p-abf68a] Thou art the Lord who gives all living things their breath,  \n> The crowned King of the sons of light, defying death.  \n> \n> [p-d0845f] No first beginning and no final end is Thine,  \n> Forever free from chains of time, Thy splendors shine.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [Chapter 14: Aaftab](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/14-aaftab/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [Aaftab](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/14-aaftab/translation/#p-77dda1). (English translation; original Urdu and transliteration also available in the corpus.)",
